#<ThaCampin'Dutchpack>

    #<Description>

        By Aaron0000

        Replaces a large number of items in the game with ports and interpretations of ThaCampin'Dutchman's arsenal from Borderlands 1.

        Notes;

        Some items have options available to them, such as which item it replaces, or an alternate skin and such.

        One of the items in this mod (Thermogenesis) uses a hotfix. Be sure to merge this mod with your main patch file.

    #</Description>

    #<Individual Item Descriptions>

        #<Weapons>

            #<Bandit Weapons>

                #<Dolos>

                    Significantly increased pellet count, almost non-existent bullet speed. Increased critical hit damage.

                    Replaces Dog by default, but can also replace the RokSalt or Sledge's Shotgun instead.

                #</Dolos>

                #<Equuleus>

                    Functions like a Revolver from Borderlands 1. Consumes three ammo per shot, increased magazine size.

                    Replaces Gub.

                    Note; Allows the Gub to spawn in elements other than corrosive. Non-corrosive Gubs will be deleted if the mod isn't run.

                #</Equuleus>

                #<Hawk>

                    No recoil. Increased accuracy.

                    Replaces RokSalt by default, but can also replace the Dog or Sledge's Shotgun instead.

                #</Hawk>

                #<Ophiuchus>

                    Spawn in non-elemental only. Fires an explosive bullet that produces a different element of explosion depending on the type of enemy it hits. Consumes two ammo per shot.

                    Replaces Madhous!

                #</Ophiuchus>

                #<Sickle>

                    High fire rate. Fires in the shape of a sickle.

                    Replaces Jolly Roger.

                #</Sickle>

                #<Traitor>

                    x4 projectile count, very high fire reate, reduced accuracy, massize magazine size. Shooting once will attempt to empty the entire magazine of ammo.

                    Replaces Tattler by default, but can also replace the Bone Shredder or Orc instead.

                #</Traitor>

                #<Vulcan Fury>

                    Incredible fire rate and magazine size. Minimal accuracy, slow projectile speed.

                    Replaces CHOPPER.

                    Note; There are two versions of the Vulcan Fury, one for use with the Unofficial Community Patch (on by default), and for use without it.

                #</Vulcan Fury>

                #<Zodiac>

                    x12 projectile count, reduced damage per projectile. Massive magazine size. Fires E-Tech projectiles that produce smaller projectiles during flight. Consumes two ammo per shot.

                    Replaces Badaboom by default, but can also replace the Roaster instead.

                #</Zodiac>

            #</Bandit Weapons>

            #<Dahl Weapons>

                #<Altair>

                    x3 projectiles, reduced damage per projectile.

                    Replaces Sloth.

                #</Altair>

                #<Barracuda>

                    Dual element - Shock Bullet, Explosive splash. Rounds twist in flight, as well as ricochet off surfaces. Increased fire rate. Shock only.

                    Replaces Veruc.

                #</Barracuda>

                #<Komodo>

                    Four-round burst-fire outside of scopes. Divides into multiple rounds on impact that ricochet multiple times. Increased elemental damage and chance. Corrosive only.

                    Replaces Dahlminator by default, but can also replace the Teapot or Hornet instead.

                #</Komodo>

            #</Dahl Weapons>

            #<Hyperion Weapons>

                #<Agonizer>

                    Explodes on contact with an enemy, penetrates enemies.

                    Replaces Logan's gun.

                #</Agonizer>

                #<Hitman>

                    Impeccable accuracy, high damage, low fire rate.

                    Replaces Morningstar by default, but can also replace the Fremington's Edge or Invader instead.

                #</Hitman>

                #<Steve>

                    HEYO!

                    Replaces Bane

                    Note; Enables the Bane to spawn without an element. Non-elemental Banes will be deleted if you don't run the mod.

                #</Steve>

                #<Wildfire>

                    Incendiary only. Increased elemental effects. Has a unique firing pattern.

                    Replaces Heartbreaker.

                    Note; Enables Heartbreaker to spawn with sights. Sighted Heartbreakers will be deleted if you don't run the mod.

                #</Wildfire>

                #<Vanquish>

                    x2 projectiles. Reduced damage per projectile. Increased critical hit damage

                    Replaces Bitch.

                #</Vanquish>

                #<Black Death>

                    Creates a veritable hell of bullets upon ricohetting off a surface.

                    Replaces Conference Call.

                #</Black Death>

                #<Fusillation>

                    Consumes 6 ammo per shot. Increased critical hit damage, reduced fire rate. Fires a large swath of projectiles.

                    Replaces Yellow Jacket by default, but can also replace the Commerce instead.

                    Note; Enables the Yellow Jacket to spawn in all elements. Non-Shock Yellow Jackets will be deleted if the mod is not run.

                #</Fusillation>

                #<Oneshot>

                    Extremely high damage, critical hit damage, and accuracy. Extrememly low fire rate and reload speed. Magazine size of 1. Consumes 5 ammo per shot. Only spawns with Hyperion parts.

                    Replaces Invader by default, but can also replace Fremington's Edge or the Morningstar instead.

                #</Oneshot>

            #</Hyperion Weapons>

            #<Jakobs Weapons>

                #<Cricket>

                    High knockback.

                    Replaces Judge by default, but can also replace the Law, Rex, Maggie, or Unforgiven instead.

                #</Cricket>

                #<Headbanger>

                    x2 projectiles.

                    Replaces Skullmasher by default, but can also replace the Trespasser or Hawkeye instead.

                #</Headbanger>

                #<Sawed-Off>

                    High projectile count, increased damage. Minimal accuracy, magazine size of 2. Consumes 2 ammo per shot. Projectiles had a very short life span.

                    Replaces Striker by default, but can also replace Triquetra, Tidal Wave, or Hydra instead.

                #</Sawed-Off>

                #<Triple>

                    Burst-fires three shots in rapid succession.

                    Replaces Maggie by default, but can also replace Law, Rex, Judge, or Unforgiven instead.

                #</Triple>

                #<Money Shot>

                    Consumes 4 ammo per shot. Fires in the shape of a $ sign, produces money upon shooting a surface.

                    Replaces Triquetra by default, but can also replace Tidal Wave, Hydra, or Striker instead.

                    Note; To achieve the money drop effect, the Landscaper's mines had to be modified. Either use a Landscaper weapon replacer, or disable the money drops.

                #</Money Shot>

                #<Railgun>

                    High damage and critical hit damage. Fires E-Tech projectiles. Consumes 2 ammo per shot.

                    Replaces Godfinger.

                    Note; There is an optional version of the skin with stronger glow in the Skins folder.

                #</Railgun>

            #</Jakobs Weapons>

            #<Maliwan Weapons>

                #<Earthquake>

                    Explosive only. Ricochets upon hitting a surface.

                    Replaces Chere-Amie.

                    Note; Forces the Chere-Amie to spawn without an elemental part. Will remain as such even if the mod is not run. Does not affect existing Chere-Amies.

                #</Earthquake>

                #<Immolator>

                    Consumes 2 ammo per shot, boosted elemental damage and chance. Incendiary only.

                    Replaces Rubi.

                #</Immolator>

                #<Behemoth>

                    High damage. Burst-fires three projectiles at a time when not using the sight, burst-fires the entire magazine when using the sight.

                    Replaces Norfleet.

                #</Behemoth>

                #<Blue Falcon>

                    Produces a large Nova upon striking a surface. Increased damage and melee damage, reduced fire rate.

                    Replaces Volcano.

                #</Blue Falcon>

                #<Salvation>

                    Heals allies when shooting them. Produces transfusion orbs upon shooting enemies. Passively restores health and ammunition. Actual damage to enemies is splash only.

                    Replaces Wanderlust.

                #</Salvation>

                #<Thermogenesis>

                    Consumes 5 ammo per shot. Fires a powerful, slow-moving laser that erupts 8 times upon striking a surface. Slow fire rate, massively increased burn damage and chance.

                    Replaces Pyrophobia.

                    Note; This weapon uses the Logan's Gun projectile to achieve the erupting effect. Either use a Logan's Gun weapon replacer when using this weapon, or avoid using the Logan's Gun.

                #</Thermogenesis>

            #</Maliwan Weapons>

            #<Tediore Weapons>

                #<Bastion>

                    Passively regenerates rocket launcher ammo.

                    Replaces Bunny.

                #</Bastion>

                #<Garrison>

                    x4 projectiles, low accuracy.

                    Replaces Gunerang.

                #</Garrison>

                #<Apollo>

                    Fires in the shape of a triangle pointing in one of four directions.

                    Replaces Octo.

                #</Apollo>

            #</Tediore Weapons>

            #<Torgue Weapons>

                #<Abaddon>

                    Dual element - Corrosive projectile, explosive splash.

                    Replaces Boom Puppy by default, but can also replace the Kerblaster or Seeker instead.

                #</Abaddon>

                #<Hand Cannon>

                    High damage, low fire rate, increased projectile speed.

                    Replaces Devastator.

                    Note; Normal Torgue pistols were originally called Hand Cannons. They are renamed to "Explistol" when this weapon is enabled.

                #</Hand Cannon>

                #<Neurokill>

                    Increased critical hit damage and projectile speed.

                    Replaces Evil Smasher.

                #</Neurokill>

                #<Cruncher>

                    Dual element - Incendiary projectile, explosive splash. Consumes four ammo per shot. Minimal accuracy, increased fire rate.

                    Replaces Landscaper by default, but can also replace the Flakker instead.

                #</Cruncher>

                #<Lacerta>

                    Consumes four ammo per shot. Fires a slow moving projectile that divides and multiple projectiles after a short period of time.

                    Replaces Seeker by default, but can also replace the Boom Puppy or Kerblaster instead.

                #</Lacerta>

                #<Javelin>

                    Fires homing rockets. Weapon damage is significantly higher than actual damage of the weapon.

                    Replaces 12 Pounder by default, but can also replace the Creamer, Nukem, Tunguska, or Ahab instead.

                #</Javelin>

                #<Painbringer>

                    Functions like a revolver from Borderlands 1. Consumes 3 ammo per shot. Dual element - Shock projectile, explosive splash. Increased reload speed. Large explosion radius.

                    Replaces Pocket Rocket.

                    Note; Has an option for an alternative skin.

                #</Painbringer>

            #</Torgue Weapons>

            #<Vladof Weapons>

                #<Cerberus>

                    x3 projectiles. Fires in the shape of a triangle. Consumes two ammo per shot.

                    Replaces Infinity by default, but can also replace the Stalker instead.

                #</Cerberus>

                #<Guerilla>

                    Significantly increased fire rate, increased weapon stability.

                    Replaces Patriot.

                #</Guerilla>

                #<Laelaps>

                    Increases movement speed when held.

                    Replaces Veritas by default, but can also replace the Stinger instead.

                #</Laelaps>

                #<Spitfire>

                    Consumes 3 ammo per shot. x8 projectiles. Reduced damage per projectile, minimal accuracy.

                    Replaces Shredifier by default, but can also replace the Rapier instead.

                #</Spitfire>

                #<Artemis>

                    Incendiary only. Fires a bullet that almost immediately divides into a corrosive bullet. Increased critical hit damage.

                    Replaces Lead Storm.

                    Note; The second bullet doesn't immediately spawn. Don't use it too close to an enemy or it may not have time to spawn.

                #</Artemis>

                #<Defiance>

                    Fires arccing projectiles. High fire rate, reduced damage and accuracy, huge magazine size, passively regenerates rocket ammo.

                    Replaces Mongol.

                #</Defiance>

                #<Spider-34>

                    Fires in the shape of a spider.

                    Replaces Stalker by default, but can also replace the Infinity instead.

                #</Spider-34>

            #</Vladof Weapons>

        #</Weapons>

        #<Shields>

            #<Aegis>

                Quickly regenerates health and ammo.

                Replaces Cradle.

            #</Aegis>

            #<Escutcheon>

                Regenerates ammo for the entire team.

                Replaces Cracked Sash

            #</Escutcheon>

            #<Flatline>

                Has a capacity of 1, no ability to recharge passively. Lowers fight For your Life Time down to the minimum. Produces a powerful nuclear explosion upon going into Fight for your Life.

                Replaces Deadly Bloom.

                Note; Enables Deadly Bloom to spawn with non-explosive elemental resistance capacitors. Deadly Blooms with elemental resistance parts will be deleted if the mod is not run.

            #</Flatline>

            #<Evergreen>

                Increases movement speed and capacity for every person that has this shield equipped.

                Replaces Hoplite.

            #</Evergreen>

            #<Godspeed>

                No shield capacity. Dramatically increases movement speed. Chance to reflect bullets.

                Replaces Transformer.

            #</Godspeed>

            #<Primrose>

                Low capacity, regenerates 12.5% of your health every second. Increases Action Skill cooldown rate.

                Replaces Neogenator.

            #</Primrose>

            #<Undying>

                High capacity, no health penalty. Significantly extends Fight for your Life time.

                Replaces Fabled Tortoise.

            #</Undying>

        #</Shields>

        #<Class Mods>

            #<Salvador Class Mods>

                #<Alucard>

                    Trades off gun capacilities for extreme melee capacilities. Increases movement speed significantly when Gunzerking.

                    Replaces Legendary Berserker.

                #</Alucard>

                #<Alexander Anderson>

                    Extreme tanking capabilities.

                    Replaces Legendary Titan.

                #</Alexander Anderson>

            #</Salvador Class Mods>

            #<Axton Class Mods>

                #<Iscariot>

                    Significant boosts to Sabre Turret skills and cooldown.

                    Replaces Legendary Engineer.

                #</Iscariot>

                #<The Captain>

                    Very high health-based boosts and survival skills.

                    Replaces Legendary Pointman.

                #</The Captain>

                #<The Major>

                    Boosts many offensive stats and offensive skills.

                    Replaces Legendary Ranger.

                #</The Major>

            #</Axton Class Mods>

            #<Zer0 Class Mods>

                #<Casull>

                    High supportive-passive boosts and passive skill boosts.

                    Replaces Slayer of Terramorphous.

                #</Casull>

                #<Blackbird>

                    Strong boosts to the entire team's damaging abilities, and boosts to sniping skills.

                    Replaces Legendary Sniper.

                #</Blackbird>

                #<Schrödinger>

                    Increases Action Skill cooldown greatly. Boosts Deception-based skills.

                    Replaces Legendary Hunter.

                #</Schrödinger>

            #</Zer0 Class Mods>

            #<Maya Class Mods>

                #<Incognito>

                    Boosts shield capabilities na dshock reisstance. Boosts shield-focused skills.

                    Replaces Legendary Nurse

                #</Incognito>

                #<Integra>

                    Boosts the entire team's critical hit damage, recoil reduction, and ammo regeneration. Increased SMG ammo regeneration for the wearer. Boosts offensive skills.

                    Replaces Legendary Cat.

                #</Integra>

                #<Seras Victoria>

                    Increases the team's Damage over Time damage and chance, as well as resistance to it. Boosts elemental skills.

                    Replaces Legendary Binder.

                #</Seras Victoria>

            #</Maya Class Mods>

            #<Gaige Class Mods>

                #<Dandywoman>

                    Boosts several offensive stats and skills.

                    Replaces Slayer of Terramorphous.

                #</Dandywoman>

                #<The Doctor>

                    Passively restores health and ammunition for the entire team as well as action skill cooldown time. Boosts survival skills.

                    Replaces Legendary Catalyst.

                #</The Doctor>

                #<Bot of Hermes>

                    Increases Action Skill Cooldown Rate by an incredible amount. Boosts Deathtrap-focused skills.

                    Replaces Legendary Roboteer.

                #</Bot of Hermes>

            #</Gaige Class Mods>

            #<Krieg Class Mods>

                #<Hellsing>

                    Boosts team melee damage, gun damage, and ammo regeneration. Boosts melee skills.

                    Replaces Legendary Sickle.

                #</Hellsing>

                #<Section XIII>

                    Increases team health, health regeneration, and shield recharge rate. Boosts survival skills.

                    Replaces Slayer of Terramorphous.

                #</Section XIII>

                #<Deus Ex Machina>

                    Boosts Explosive and Grenade Damage, cuts Rocket Launcher damage in half. Passively regenerates rockets rapidly. Boosts explosion-focused skills.

                    Replaces Legendary Reaper.

                #</Deus Ex Machina>

            #</Krieg Class Mods>

        #</Class Mods>

    #</Individual Item Descriptions>

    #<Weapons>

        #<Bandit>

            #<Legendary>

                #<Dolos><MUT>

                    #<Dog replacer (Default)>

                        #<Name/Red Text>

                            set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Barrel.SG_Barrel_Bandit_Dog GestaltModeSkeletalMeshName SG_Barrel_Torgue

                            set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Name.Title.Title__Unique_Dog PartName Dolos

                            set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Name.Title.Title__Unique_Dog:AttributePresentationDefinition_8 NoConstraintText You just activated my trap card!

                        #</Name/Red Text>

                        #<Rarity>

                            set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Barrel.SG_Barrel_Bandit_Dog rarity (basevalueattribute=none)

                            set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Barrel.SG_Barrel_Bandit_Dog rarity (BaseValueConstant=5)

                        #</Rarity>

                        #<Stats>

                            set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Barrel.SG_Barrel_Bandit_Dog WeaponAttributeEffects ((AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponShotCost',ModifierType=MT_PreAdd,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=3.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponProjectilesPerShot',ModifierType=MT_PreAdd,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=24.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponClipSize',ModifierType=MT_PreAdd,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=2.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponFireInterval',ModifierType=MT_PreAdd,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=0.000000,BaseValueAttribute=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.WeaponManufacturer.Weapon_Is_Torgue',InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=-0.050000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponDamage',ModifierType=MT_Scale,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=0.000000,BaseValueAttribute=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.WeaponManufacturer.Weapon_Is_Torgue',InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=0.200000)),(AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.Weapon.WeaponProjectileSpeedMultiplier',ModifierType=MT_Scale,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=-125.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)))

                            set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Barrel.SG_Barrel_Bandit_Dog ExternalAttributeEffects ((AttributeToModify=AttributeDefinition'D_Attributes.GameplayAttributes.PlayerCriticalHitBonus',ModifierType=MT_Scale,BaseModifierValue=(BaseValueConstant=0.500000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)))

                            set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Barrel.SG_Barrel_Bandit_Dog AttributeSlotUpgrades ((SlotName="WeaponSpread",GradeIncrease=-34,bActivateSlot=True),(SlotName="AccuracyMin",GradeIncrease=-4,bActivateSlot=True),(SlotName="WeaponDamage",GradeIncrease=7,bActivateSlot=True),(SlotName="WeaponAccuracyImpulse",GradeIncrease=-14,bActivateSlot=True),(SlotName="WeaponFireRate",GradeIncrease=-12,bActivateSlot=True),(SlotName="WeaponMagSize",GradeIncrease=2,bActivateSlot=True))

                        #</Stats>

                        #<Skin>

                            set Common_GunMaterials.Materials.Shotgun.Mati_BanditSG_3_Dog ScalarParameterValues ((ParameterName="p_HighlightsIntensity",ParameterValue=0.500000,ExpressionGUID=(A=-1257568432,B=1277066486,C=-723473993,D=-1144384173)),(ParameterName="p_ShadowsIntensity",ParameterValue=1.000000,ExpressionGUID=(A=437293753,B=1205147708,C=-775723903,D=1480014964)),(ParameterName="p_DecalRotate",ParameterValue=-0.006800,ExpressionGUID=(A=-276527909,B=1298581551,C=856978878,D=743944047)),(ParameterName="p_UseFullColorDecal",ParameterValue=0.000000,ExpressionGUID=(A=-1064329812,B=1077705328,C=339664807,D=1869745420)),(ParameterName="p_ReplaceDecal",ParameterValue=1.000000,ExpressionGUID=(A=85863466,B=1257609701,C=-728575820,D=1337098176)))

                            set Common_GunMaterials.Materials.Shotgun.Mati_BanditSG_3_Dog TextureParameterValues ((ParameterName="p_Masks",ParameterValue=Texture2D'Weap_Shotguns.Tex.Weap_Shotgun_Comp',ExpressionGUID=(A=-330624041,B=1167251458,C=-335191907,D=-166684394)),(ParameterName="p_Diffuse",ParameterValue=Texture2D'Common_GunMaterials.CompTextures.Weap_LauncherShotgunPistol_Comp',ExpressionGUID=(A=1757607260,B=1326539502,C=-317215581,D=-565807463)),(ParameterName="p_NormalScopesEmissive",ParameterValue=Texture2D'Weap_Shotguns.Tex.Weap_Shotgun_Nor',ExpressionGUID=(A=-1743872746,B=1126171774,C=119496871,D=-1952271718)),(ParameterName="P_SimpleReflect",ParameterValue=Texture2D'Common_GunMaterials.Patterns.Pattern_Lightning',ExpressionGUID=(A=-858148940,B=1327945772,C=148462268,D=1899047224)),(ParameterName="p_Decal",ParameterValue=Texture2D'Common_GunMaterials.Logos.grundge_decals_2',ExpressionGUID=(A=-923052711,B=1309861752,C=584229786,D=-1229888527)),(ParameterName="p_Pattern",ParameterValue=Texture2D'Common_GunMaterials.Patterns.Pattern_Jakobs_CaseHardened',ExpressionGUID=(A=534250533,B=1202550002,C=1578302861,D=-717876416)))

                            set Common_GunMaterials.Materials.Shotgun.Mati_BanditSG_3_Dog VectorParameterValues ((ParameterName="p_AColorHilight",ParameterValue=(R=0.100000,G=0.100000,B=0.100000,A=1.000000),ExpressionGUID=(A=170714760,B=1132476783,C=-275668290,D=655702143)),(ParameterName="p_AColorMidtone",ParameterValue=(R=0.030000,G=0.030000,B=0.030000,A=1.000000),ExpressionGUID=(A=473594356,B=1338758895,C=824823946,D=864253813)),(ParameterName="p_AColorShadow",ParameterValue=(R=0.010000,G=0.010000,B=0.010000,A=1.000000),ExpressionGUID=(A=-429590341,B=1156435294,C=-1015192901,D=687313413)),(ParameterName="p_BColorHilight",ParameterValue=(R=1.500000,G=1.500000,B=1.500000,A=1.000000),ExpressionGUID=(A=170714760,B=1132476783,C=-275668290,D=655702143)),(ParameterName="p_BColorMidtone",ParameterValue=(R=1.000000,G=1.000000,B=1.000000,A=1.000000),ExpressionGUID=(A=473594356,B=1338758895,C=824823946,D=864253813)),(ParameterName="p_BColorShadow",ParameterValue=(R=0.660000,G=0.660000,B=0.660000,A=1.000000),ExpressionGUID=(A=-429590341,B=1156435294,C=-1015192901,D=687313413)),(ParameterName="p_CColorHilight",ParameterValue=(R=0.010000,G=0.010000,B=0.010000,A=1.000000),ExpressionGUID=(A=170714760,B=1132476783,C=-275668290,D=655702143)),(ParameterName="p_CColorMidtone",ParameterValue=(R=0.010000,G=0.010000,B=0.010000,A=1.000000),ExpressionGUID=(A=473594356,B=1338758895,C=824823946,D=864253813)),(ParameterName="p_CColorShadow",ParameterValue=(R=0.010000,G=0.001000,B=0.001000,A=1.000000),ExpressionGUID=(A=-429590341,B=1156435294,C=-1015192901,D=687313413)),(ParameterName="p_ReflectColor",ParameterValue=(R=2.742249,G=2.033009,B=1.303000,A=1.000000),ExpressionGUID=(A=295058103,B=1318551573,C=-2045449573,D=-547597976)),(ParameterName="p_ReflectionChannelScale",ParameterValue=(R=1.000000,G=4.000000,B=0.800000,A=0.000000),ExpressionGUID=(A=1869386622,B=1303200947,C=-1616405849,D=714558284)),(ParameterName="p_DecalChannel",ParameterValue=(R=0.000000,G=0.000000,B=0.000000,A=0.000000),ExpressionGUID=(A=1869386622,B=1303200947,C=-1616405849,D=714558284)),(ParameterName="p_DColor",ParameterValue=(                         #</Skin>

                    #</Dog replacer (Default)>

                    #<RokSalt replacer>

                        #<Name/Red Text>

                            #set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Barrel.SG_Barrel_Jakobs_RockSalt GestaltModeSkeletalMeshName SG_Barrel_Torgue<off>

                            #set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Name.Title.Title__Unique_RokSalt PartName Dolos<off>

                            #set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Name.Title.Title__Unique_RokSalt:AttributePresentationDefinition_8 NoConstraintText You just activated my trap card!<off>

                        #</Name/Red Text>

                        #<Rarity>

                            #set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Barrel.SG_Barrel_Jakobs_RockSalt rarity (basevalueattribute=none)<off>

                            #set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Barrel.SG_Barrel_Jakobs_RockSalt rarity (BaseValueConstant=5)<off>
